codelist.label: Cause Of death
codelist.definition: Data on causes of death (COD) provide information on mortality patterns and form a major element of public health information.
codelist.description: COD data refer to the underlying cause which - according to the World Health Organisation (WHO) - is "the disease or injury which initiated the train of morbid events leading directly to death, or the circumstances of the accident or violence which produced the fatal injury".
